{# Using Icons #}
<h2>Using icons</h2>
<p>WMN Design System icons are available as an SVG sprite to include in your HTML page.</p>
<h3>How to use</h3>
<ul>
  <li><a class="wmnds-link" target="_blank" href="$*cdn/img/wmnds-sprite.min.svg" download="wmnds-sprite.min.svg">Download the icon svg sprite</a>.</li>
  <li>Include the downloaded icon sprite in to your project locally.</li>
  <li>You can now start using the icon svg sprite sheet using the instructions below.</li>
</ul>
<p>To display an icon or glyph, use an icon tag (from the icon section at the bottom of the page) with a href attribute and xlink:href (as a fallback). Make sure that the xlink and href tags are pointing to the location of your downloaded icon sprite sheet.</p>
<pre>
  <code class="html">
    {{-
      wmndsIcon({
        icon: 'ICON-TAG-NAME'
      }) | forceescape | trim
    -}}
  </code>
</pre>
<hr>

{# Icons #}
<h2>Icons</h2>
<p>Find below a list of all our icons and their tags below. To use, don't forget to prefix the tag with 'wmnds-'</p>
<h3>General</h3>
<div class="wmnds-grid website-icons">
  {% for icon in iconGeneral %}
    <div class="wmnds-col-1-2 wmnds-col-sm-1-6 text-center">
      {{
        wmndsIcon({
          icon: 'general-' + icon
        })
      }}
      <p>{{ 'general-' + icon }}</p>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
</div>

